This is unnecessary right? dependency() automatically falls back to subprojects.

https://mesonbuild.com/Reference-manual_functions.html#dependency
shouldn't this one be called 'fru_oem_ibm.h' consistent with the other OEM headers?
Any chance we can rewrite the tests into C at some point?

Yeah this is another item that's in my list since a long time, I did try to change the tests to c, but it s bit of work[we use things like std::array, vectors e.t.c in the test - just need to convert them into c type arrays and make sure we fix all the warnings]. I can pick it up once this is migrated.
Maybe set c_std=gnu17 as well? or c17 if we can get away with it.
Added c17, this actually led me to add D_DEFAULT_SOURCE as my project argument - as without that we get complaints about functions from endian.h as implicitly declared.
Can you explain where D_DEFAULT_SOURCE comes from?

Per my understanding, functions like htobe16, htole16, be16toh, le16toh, htobe32, htole32, be32toh, le32toh, htobe64, htole64, be64toh are defined in endian.h header file and are enable through feature test macros.

For example, from man page of htole32 , defines _BSD_SOURCE , to enable these functions the BSD_SOURCE macro needs to be defined.

https://linux.die.net/man/3/htole32

And I came to know that BSD_SOURCE has been deprecated since glib version 2.18, and the later versions would need DEFAULT_SOURCE macro instead.

Can we please make this a 0 major version? That indicates the library API isn't yet stable, which is probably what we want.

See https://semver.org/#spec-item-4
per suggestions in the discord , changed it to 0.1.0 in the next patch.
Just confirming we want both of these?

yes we want both 

subdirectories -> would install all the header files in /usr/include/libpldm folder
preverse_path -> would install all the header files preserving the path for example
oem/ibm/fru_oem_ibm.h will be now installed at /usr/include/libpldm/oem/ibm/ folder.
Yes, trying to change the header locations is a separate problem. We need to leave them as is for the purpose of the subproject/split. We can move them later if we feel that's necessary.
If we set 'required: true' here we get rid of the conditional below, which cleans up the code a bit.
